 \sqrt{x+1} - \sqrt{x-1} = \sqrt{4x-1} 
x \in \mathbb{R}
x = \frac54
x+1+x-1-2\sqrt{x+1}\sqrt{x-1}=4x-1\implies(2x-1)^2=4(x^2-1)\implies
4x^2-4x+1=4x^2-4\implies 4x=5\implies x=\frac54
\sqrt{\frac54+1}-\sqrt{\frac54-1}\stackrel ?=\sqrt{5-1}\iff\frac32-\frac12=2
x=\frac54
1=2
 \begin{align} 2x-2\sqrt{x^2-1}&=4x-1\\ 1-2x&=2\sqrt{x^2-1}\\ 4x^2-4x+1&=4x^2-4\\ 5&=4x\end{align} 
(x+1)-(x-1)=2
\sqrt{x+1}-\sqrt{x-1}=\sqrt{4x-1}\ \ \ \ (1)
\sqrt{x+1}+\sqrt{x-1}=\frac2{\sqrt{4x-1}}\ \ \ \ (2)
2\sqrt{x+1}=\sqrt{4x-1}+\frac2{\sqrt{4x-1}}=\frac{4x+1}{\sqrt{4x-1}}
\implies 2\sqrt{x+1} \sqrt{4x-1}=4x+1 \ \ \ \ (3)
2x-2\sqrt{x+1}\sqrt{x-1}=4x-1
-2\sqrt{x+1}\sqrt{x-1}=2x-1
2x-1\leq0
 x\leq \dfrac12
x\geq 1
